[src:pydantic-validation/serialization] Some of them are specific to a particular Smalltalk implementation or class library.
[src:pydantic-validation/serialization] There are several ways in Squeak Smalltalk to serialize and store objects.
[src:pydantic-validation/serialization] The easiest and most used are `storeOn:/readFrom:` and binary storage formats based on `SmartRefStream` serializers.
[src:pydantic-validation/serialization] In addition, bundled objects can be stored and retrieved using `ImageSegments`.
[src:pydantic-validation/serialization] Both provide a so-called "binary-object storage framework", which support serialization into and retrieval from a compact binary form.
